- Yeong Cheol has...

315
00:09:41,830 --> 00:09:43,630
- Gongchan picked the photo.
- I see.

316
00:09:43,930 --> 00:09:45,939
Sandeul, your mouth doesn't look so protruding.

317
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:48,239
- Exactly. I was so surprised.
- I see.

318
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,639
Sandeul, cover your face.

319
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,769
Like this?

320
00:09:50,770 --> 00:09:52,379
- Yeong Cheol, stand next to him.
- I don't think so.

321
00:09:52,380 --> 00:09:53,539
- It's not protruding.
- Yeong Cheol, go ahead.

322
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:55,009
His mouth and jawline look great.

323
00:09:55,010 --> 00:09:56,779
- Sandeul must know that.
- Take a look at Yeong Cheol.

324
00:09:56,780 --> 00:09:58,956
- Is it not protruding?
- Sandeul, look at Yeong Cheol.

325
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:00,819
- Cover your eyes and nose.
- His mouth sticks out quite a bit.

326
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:02,090
Oh, goodness. I'm sorry.

327
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:03,989
- Right?
- I see the difference now.

328
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:06,060
- You see that, right?
- His mouth does stick out.

329
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:08,059
- Next up is Hanbin.
- Hanbin.

330
00:10:08,060 --> 00:10:11,230
- Young people these days...
- A Gen Z style nickname.

331
00:10:11,490 --> 00:10:13,659
Have such pretty nicknames. I'm sure his fans came up with it.

332
00:10:13,660 --> 00:10:15,130
- Sunghanbinna.
- That's right.

333
00:10:15,670 --> 00:10:17,369
- "Sunghanbinna?"
- I'm called that...

334
00:10:17,370 --> 00:10:18,869
- because I glow when I appear.
- Awesome.

335
00:10:18,870 --> 00:10:20,770
Is Hanbin your real name?

336
00:10:21,370 --> 00:10:23,909
- It's Hanbin, not Binna.
- I didn't mean that.

337
00:10:23,910 --> 00:10:25,309
- Is Sung Hanbin your real name?
- Is it your real name?

338
00:10:25,310 --> 00:10:27,740
- Yes, it's my real name.
- Your name...

339
00:10:28,410 --> 00:10:32,449
- suits your appearance perfectly.
- I agree.

340
00:10:32,450 --> 00:10:34,549
"Sung" means to achieve, "Han" means country, and "Bin" means to shine.

341
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:35,589
- Oh, my.
- The name suits him well.

342
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:37,349
- It's as if...
- He has a romance comics vibe.

343
00:10:37,350 --> 00:10:38,719
- It's as if there were...
- He does have that kind of vibe.

344
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:40,159
A comic book protagonist named Sung Hanbin...

345
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:42,130
- who looks just like Hanbin.
- Right.

346
00:10:42,530 --> 00:10:44,259
- Jang Hoon, thank you.
- What was your childhood nickname?

347
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:45,500
- My childhood nickname?
- Yes.

348
00:10:45,860 --> 00:10:48,060
I was quite chubby when I was little,

349
00:10:48,700 --> 00:10:50,700
- so I was called "Fatty."
- You were that chubby?

350
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:52,469
Look at Ho Dong's face.

351
00:10:52,470 --> 00:10:53,799
- I bet he grew taller and thinner.
- Shin Young,

352
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,169
why are you looking at Ho Dong too?

353
00:10:55,170 --> 00:10:57,169
- You shouldn't look at him.
- You shouldn't.

354
00:10:57,170 --> 00:10:58,739
How chubby were you to get that nickname?

355
00:10:58,740 --> 00:11:01,779
- I weighed almost 100kg.
- Really?

356
00:11:01,780 --> 00:11:04,009
- I slimmed down as I grew up.
- I weighed 88kg.

357
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:05,256
I stopped growing taller after that.

358
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:07,549
Does that mean I can be like him if I lose weight?

359
00:11:07,550 --> 00:11:08,849
- No.
- No, you can't.

360
00:11:08,850 --> 00:11:11,089
- You're naturally big-boned.
- Doesn't it mean that?

361
00:11:11,090 --> 00:11:12,519
- You have a different build.
- It was during his growth spurt.

362
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:15,689
- You have a different build.
- Ho Dong needs to lose bones too.

363
00:11:15,690 --> 00:11:18,059
- You need to get your bones shaved.
- He needs to lose bones and fat.

364
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:20,500
- You need to get your bones shaved.
- If Ho Dong slims down,

365
00:11:20,530 --> 00:11:22,210
- his neck will be broken.
- That's right.

366
00:11:22,370 --> 00:11:25,199
(His head would be too heavy for his neck.)

367
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,340
His face won't get slimmer.

368
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:29,370
His face won't get slimmer. It's all bone structure.

369
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:31,509
It's not fat that matters. It's his bone structure.

370
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:33,079
- Ho Dong, don't lose weight.
- Exactly.

371
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:34,879
- No, I can't let that happen.
- His neck will be broken. No way.

372
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:36,479
- I need to protect my neck.
- Right.

373
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:38,079
- You need to keep it safe.
- You need it to support your head.

374
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,296
- Next...
- I shouldn't lose weight.

375
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:42,719
We'll find out where our four guests belong to.

376
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,649
- Let's go.
- First up is Soyou.

377
00:11:44,650 --> 00:11:46,219
Everyone knows about this. It's "SOYOUGI."

378
00:11:46,220 --> 00:11:47,519
- Right.
- Your YouTube channel.

379
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:49,480
- That's right.
- You're still running it, right?

380
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:52,729
(Soyou shares her healthy lifestyle on "SOYOUGI.")

381
00:11:52,730 --> 00:11:55,599
You work out in many of your videos on your channel.

382
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:57,469
I learned about stair climbers while watching your videos.

383
00:11:57,470 --> 00:11:59,439
- Really?
- You worked out a lot.

384
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,199
- You lost a lot of weight too.
- She got much thinner.

385
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,769
- I was surprised when I saw her.
- That's right.

386
00:12:02,770 --> 00:12:04,069
Why did you lose so much weight?

387
00:12:04,070 --> 00:12:06,840
I released the song "PDA" last year.

388
00:12:07,180 --> 00:12:10,980
Since dance performances often involve revealing outfits,

389
00:12:11,150 --> 00:12:13,579
- you look better with a toned body.
- It makes you look sexy.

390
00:12:13,580 --> 00:12:15,850
I transform my body...

391
00:12:16,390 --> 00:12:17,890
to match the music genre.

392
00:12:18,350 --> 00:12:21,190
When I released a dance song, I covered up for my performance,

393
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:23,830
and my body looked a bit bulky because I had big muscles.

394
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:26,400
You see, I usually do a lot of weight training.

395
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:30,499
But last year, I mainly focused on bodyweight workouts...

396
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,929
and did a lot of cardio.

397
00:12:31,930 --> 00:12:34,250
- How much weight did you lose?
- It helps to lose weight.

398
00:12:34,470 --> 00:12:35,710
I lost 20kg.

399
00:12:36,110 --> 00:12:38,770
- That can't be true.
- You lost 20kg?

400
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:41,580
What matters is how long it took you to lose that much.

401
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:43,549
- Six months?
- I think it took about six months.

402
00:12:43,550 --> 00:12:45,049
