- It's "Girl."

466
00:15:17,870 --> 00:15:18,999
- "Girl."
- "Girl."

467
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:22,870
You will find my new song very unexpected.

468
00:15:22,970 --> 00:15:24,810
- Really?
- It's something I've never tried.

469
00:15:25,070 --> 00:15:30,510
(Soyou is back with her third EP "Off Hours.")

470
00:15:30,610 --> 00:15:32,050
As for Gi Kwang...

471
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:34,149
- I'm glad you're here, Gi Kwang.
- Oh, right.

472
00:15:34,150 --> 00:15:35,320
He wrote, "BEAST."

473
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:37,349
Gi Kwang, you're back.

474
00:15:37,350 --> 00:15:39,819
I was there with you guys when you were...

475
00:15:39,820 --> 00:15:42,729
brainstorming names for the group.

476
00:15:42,730 --> 00:15:44,830
- When?
- I suggested "Highlight..."

477
00:15:45,130 --> 00:15:47,999
Soo Geun didn't give them an idea. But I actually gave them...

478
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,270
a piece of advice back then.

479
00:15:49,430 --> 00:15:50,430
- What did you say?
- You remember that, right?

480
00:15:50,430 --> 00:15:51,430
- What did you say?
- He doesn't seem to remember it.

481
00:15:51,431 --> 00:15:53,246
- He doesn't remember it at all.
- He doesn't remember that.

482
00:15:53,270 --> 00:15:54,946
- Did he force his idea on them?
- I bet his advice wasn't memorable.

483
00:15:54,970 --> 00:15:57,369
- I asked them to come to MBC...
- Yes?

484
00:15:57,370 --> 00:15:59,509
And said that if you couldn't use the name BEAST,

485
00:15:59,510 --> 00:16:00,780
you should go with "A-ST."

486
00:16:01,340 --> 00:16:03,049
- Oh, I remember that.
- You remember that, right?

487
00:16:03,050 --> 00:16:04,179
- I remember that now.
- "A-ST" instead of "BEAST?"

488
00:16:04,180 --> 00:16:05,579
- More than the name "BEAST..."
- "A-ST" because it's "BEAST?"

489
00:16:05,580 --> 00:16:07,550
When I heard the name "A-ST,".

490
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:10,120
I didn't really listen to what he said.

491
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:11,949
- He didn't listen.
- Right.

492
00:16:11,950 --> 00:16:14,519
- "So that's his opinion."
- It would've been a terrible name.

493
00:16:14,520 --> 00:16:15,789
- The meaning was good, though.
- Right.

494
00:16:15,790 --> 00:16:17,659
- They couldn't use "BEAST."
- "Highlight" is the best.

495
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:18,959
So they should move up from B to A.

496
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:20,460
Now you can perform BEAST's songs...

497
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:23,299
- We could sing our songs.
- Right?

498
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:24,999
- You couldn't use the name.
- We couldn't use the name "BEAST."

499
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,740
The negotiation went well this time.

500
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:28,369
We reclaimed our old group name.

501
00:16:28,370 --> 00:16:29,930
- That's a relief.
- That's great news.

502
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:32,209
- That's such great news.
- It's a massive accomplishment.

503
00:16:32,210 --> 00:16:33,809
Are you guys working as BEAST now?

504
00:16:33,810 --> 00:16:36,449
Now, we can choose between BEAST and Highlight...

505
00:16:36,450 --> 00:16:38,650
- as our group name.
- Yes.

506
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:40,619
- We worked for seven years...
- It was a long time ago.

507
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:42,149
- as BEAST.
- Right.

508
00:16:42,150 --> 00:16:43,919
And we used the name "Highlight" for nine years.

509
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,349
- You used it for a longer time.
- That's right.

510
00:16:45,350 --> 00:16:47,059
"Highlight" became an older name than "BEAST."

511
00:16:47,060 --> 00:16:48,859
- So we thought...
- I see.

512
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:51,090
"Highlight" was the name that truly defined us.

513
00:16:51,330 --> 00:16:54,929
The other members and I decided to stick with "Highlight."

514
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:55,969
- But...
- How about "Hi-BEAST..."

515
00:16:55,970 --> 00:16:57,050
with "hi" as in a greeting?

516
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:58,529
- What?
- "Hi..."

517
00:16:58,530 --> 00:17:00,469
He's suggesting a combined word of the two names.

518
00:17:00,470 --> 00:17:01,639
- I will...
- That's a good idea.

519
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:04,120
- review it in a positive light.
- What are you talking about?

520
00:17:04,310 --> 00:17:05,939
- Stop lying!
- What are you talking about?

521
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:07,639
- You're lying.
- Don't review it.

522
00:17:07,640 --> 00:17:09,449
- Was it obvious?
- You're lying.

523
00:17:09,450 --> 00:17:10,926
- Just don't give it a thought.
- Was that a lie?

524
00:17:10,950 --> 00:17:12,249
- Are you serious?
- Why? It's a good idea.

525
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:13,579
- A combined word.
- No, it's not a good idea.

526
00:17:13,580 --> 00:17:14,749
- The two universes merge.
- Hanbin.

527
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:16,449
- "Highlight" and "BEAST."
- That's right.

528
00:17:16,450 --> 00:17:19,220
- He's forgetting what he hears.
- You can use "hi" as in a greeting.

529
00:17:19,420 --> 00:17:20,900
Should I receive the idea he dropped?

530
00:17:21,320 --> 00:17:23,859
Hanbin is catching what went in one ear and out the other.

531
00:17:23,860 --> 00:17:25,589
- Exactly.
- I should put it in my backpack.

532
00:17:25,590 --> 00:17:26,729
Right. Thank you.

533
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:27,929
This is how young people these days react.

534
00:17:27,930 --> 00:17:30,269
Hanbin's reaction is a typical Gen Z reaction.

535
00:17:30,270 --> 00:17:31,999
Back in my days, we were like, "What is he talking about?"

536
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:33,969
- But these days, young people...
- He picked up what he dropped.

537
00:17:33,970 --> 00:17:35,210
Would make a gesture like this.

538
00:17:35,340 --> 00:17:36,469
That's how the fifth generation reacts.

539
00:17:36,470 --> 00:17:38,286
- That's right.
- I should've reacted like that.

540
00:17:38,310 --> 00:17:41,880
Won't you hold a concert as BEAST?

541
00:17:42,340 --> 00:17:44,709
We need to release a new album before holding a concert.

542
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:47,449
- But we're not...
- You're not working as a group?

543
00:17:47,450 --> 00:17:49,689
- I want them to come back.
- We're taking our time with it.

544
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:52,959
We're determined to make a really good album this time.

545
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,360
We're currently collecting songs.

546
00:17:54,690 --> 00:17:56,606
How many songs do you usually review for an album?

547
00:17:56,630 --> 00:17:58,489
I think we usually review about 60 songs.

548
00:17:58,490 --> 00:17:59,829
Sang Min said he was writing songs too.

549
00:17:59,830 --> 00:18:01,790
- Sang Min writes songs too.
- I write songs too.

550
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,246
All right. He doesn't want them.

551
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:04,829
- He refused to review the songs.
- Sang Min.

552
00:18:04,830 --> 00:18:06,639
- Your idea ruined your image.
- He refused.

553
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:09,540
- I'll send you about three songs.
- Three songs? Sounds great.

554
00:18:09,710 --> 00:18:10,809
- I'll take a listen...
- Really?

555
00:18:10,810 --> 00:18:15,340
- and review the songs.
- Do you work with a stylist?

556
00:18:15,510 --> 00:18:17,009
- Yes, we work with a stylist.
- Why?

557
00:18:17,010 --> 00:18:18,079
- Why?
- It's just...

558
00:18:18,080 --> 00:18:21,549
- Did our outfits not look good?
- The stylist I'm working with...

559
00:18:21,550 --> 00:18:22,889
- used to work with BEAST.
- That's right.

560
00:18:22,890 --> 00:18:23,949
- Really?
- Yes.

561
00:18:23,950 --> 00:18:25,890
You can hire the stylist if you want.

562
00:18:26,820 --> 00:18:28,059
- What about you?
- What does that mean?

563
00:18:28,060 --> 00:18:29,429
I don't need much styling often.

564
00:18:29,430 --> 00:18:31,159
- Is this a flea market?
- What is this...

565
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:33,506
- I mean, that's an option.
- They're really like a family.

566
00:18:33,530 --> 00:18:35,729
- I was so surprised.
- I met her.

567
00:18:35,730 --> 00:18:37,069
- You met her, right?
- Yes, I greeted her.

568
00:18:37,070 --> 00:18:40,040
- Really?
- Kyung Hoon has the Highlight vibe.

569
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:43,309
- Right. I see that.
- His makeup is similar to theirs.

570
00:18:43,310 --> 00:18:46,580
On this show, Kyung Hoon always takes the highlight.

571
00:18:47,580 --> 00:18:50,179
Kyung Hoon's dance has a similar vibe to Highlight.

572
00:18:50,180 --> 00:18:52,249
- Right. I see the similarity.
- Our universes are connected.

573
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:55,019
- He looks like Yoon Du Jun as well.
- They're connected to each other.

574
00:18:55,020 --> 00:18:56,619
- I didn't realize that.
- He looks like Du Jun.

575
00:18:56,620 --> 00:18:58,796
- He looks like Du Jun, indeed.
- You've been writing songs.

576
00:18:58,820 --> 00:19:00,190
We always work on a new song.

577
00:19:00,520 --> 00:19:02,259
I think we'll release a new song sometime this year.

578
00:19:02,260 --> 00:19:05,090
- This year?
- Why don't you give songs to him?

579
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:08,399
- Our musical styles are different.
- We like rock ballad songs too.

580
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,499
- He's good at it.
- I see.

581
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:11,599
Then after the shoot...

582
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:13,840
- Send them through the stylist.
- Right. I'll do that.

583
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,269
- And if you don't need the stylist, - Take my stylist...

584
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:17,710
send the stylist my way.

585
00:19:18,410 --> 00:19:20,256
- Send the stylist or...
- Do one of those for him.

586
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:21,739
- Send the stylist to him or...
- Okay. Got it.

587
00:19:21,740 --> 00:19:23,349
- Send me your songs.
- You don't need more information.

588
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:24,679
- Because we both know that person.
- That's right.

589
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,126
- Next up is...
- You both know the stylist.

590
00:19:26,150 --> 00:19:30,350
Sandeul wrote that he belonged to B1A4 Company.

591
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:31,889
- You started your own agency.
- Is that a real agency?

592
00:19:31,890 --> 00:19:32,960
Yes, we did.

593
00:19:33,790 --> 00:19:36,359
- Congratulations.
- CNU, Gongchan, and I...

594
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:38,059
co-founded B1A4 Company.

595
00:19:38,060 --> 00:19:40,560
- I see.
- Congrats. I didn't know that.

596
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:42,090
Where is your office located?

597
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,330
- Our office?
- Yes.

598
00:19:44,230 --> 00:19:45,599
You can say we don't have one.

599
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,139
- Is it a paper company?
- You don't have a physical office?

600
00:19:47,140 --> 00:19:48,369
- Maybe it's a paper company.
- An office...

601
00:19:48,370 --> 00:19:52,240
- Is it a paper company?
- I mean, we do have an office...

602
00:19:52,570 --> 00:19:55,639
We have an expert here. You should consult with Sang Min...

603
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:57,309
- and ask for some advice.
- That's right.

604
00:19:57,310 --> 00:20:00,220
- That's right.
- He's been producing an idol group.

605
00:20:00,580 --> 00:20:03,340
- He's doing well financially now.
- Really? Is he producing a group?

606
00:20:04,190 --> 00:20:07,290
I'll give you some practical advice. First, you need an office.

607
00:20:07,420 --> 00:20:08,689
- I do have one.
- He has one.

608
00:20:08,690 --> 00:20:11,929
Did you register as a cultural content business?

609
00:20:11,930 --> 00:20:13,899
- Yes.
- Right? Perfect.

610
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:15,159
- Of course.
- What about investment?

611
00:20:15,160 --> 00:20:16,629
- The capital.
- Capital.

612
00:20:16,630 --> 00:20:18,299
- Capital...
- From the members?

613
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,139
- Do the members...
- This is important.

614
00:20:20,140 --> 00:20:21,700
Have equal shares in the company?

615
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:23,710
- Yes, equal shares.
- Equal shares?

616
00:20:23,810 --> 00:20:25,269
What's best is...

617
00:20:25,270 --> 00:20:27,750
to give each 30 percent and invite someone to take 10 percent.

618
00:20:28,580 --> 00:20:29,740
And there's your ten percent.

619
00:20:29,950 --> 00:20:31,390
If I were to take the ten percent...

620
00:20:31,850 --> 00:20:33,050
And there's your ten percent.

621
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:34,549
If I were to take the ten percent...

622
00:20:34,550 --> 00:20:37,249
- Something smells fishy.
- He's your typical scammer.

623
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:38,349
- No.
- Hold on.

624
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:39,389
If you think about it...

625
00:20:39,390 --> 00:20:41,159
- Because...
- How creative.

626
00:20:41,160 --> 00:20:42,689
- That's how you run a business.
- Listen.

627
00:20:42,690 --> 00:20:44,159
Gi Kwang started such a structure first.

628
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,590
- True.
- Yes.

629
00:20:45,790 --> 00:20:47,830
He just said you're a typical scammer.

630
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:50,299
I met plenty of people like him.

631
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:53,139
- Is that so?
- People who will bring in...

632
00:20:53,140 --> 00:20:54,499
- Bring in money.
- investment from China,

633
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,899
- Right.
- work with a certain somebody,

634
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,939
- Investment...
- and...

635
00:20:57,940 --> 00:20:59,479
sign up with actor Tony Leung.

636
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:01,010
- I met a handful of them.
- I see.

637
00:21:01,380 --> 00:21:02,780
- Be careful.
- He's right.

638
00:21:03,210 --> 00:21:05,709
Don't worry about investment. We have Hana Bank...

639
00:21:05,710 --> 00:21:07,520
- Is that so?
- and Long Cash here.

640
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:10,390
- Long Cash.
- Come on.

641
00:21:10,450 --> 00:21:12,420
He guarantees a long loan period.

642
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,619
Long Cash? I get it.

643
00:21:14,620 --> 00:21:16,559
- There's not even an interest.
- No.

644
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:18,529
- There's no interest.
- No interest?

645
00:21:18,530 --> 00:21:19,899
There may be no interest,

646
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:21,699
but he hates nonsense.

647
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:23,530
- Is that so?
- No interest?

648
00:21:24,170 --> 00:21:25,599
- It's true.
- I want a loan with no interest.

649
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:26,839
- Our company...
- What I hate the most...

650
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:27,840
will be in Heukseok-dong.

651
00:21:27,841 --> 00:21:29,670
Are useless comments.

652
00:21:30,410 --> 00:21:32,309
- You know, unnecessary talks.
- Unnecessary talks?

653
00:21:32,310 --> 00:21:33,609
He hates them. Just pay him back...

654
00:21:33,610 --> 00:21:34,909
- on the promised date.
- Of course.

655
00:21:34,910 --> 00:21:35,939
On time.

656
00:21:35,940 --> 00:21:39,679
It's been over 10 years since B1A4 has worked...

657
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:41,679
- together.
- Correct.

658
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:42,889
You'll end up fighting...

659
00:21:42,890 --> 00:21:44,049
- while doing business.
- Right.

660
00:21:44,050 --> 00:21:45,219
We might not be on the same page.

661
00:21:45,220 --> 00:21:46,859
Was there such a time while working together?

662
00:21:46,860 --> 00:21:47,919
When it comes to us...

663
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:50,489
I'm the second oldest, which makes me the middleman.

664
00:21:50,490 --> 00:21:53,260
When something doesn't get agreed upon,

665
00:21:53,500 --> 00:21:56,769
I become the go-between.

666
00:21:56,770 --> 00:22:00,499
We never had a time when we didn't agree on something.

667
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:01,539
Didn't you have a ton?

668
00:22:01,540 --> 00:22:02,639
- You're wrong.
- There was a bunch.

669
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:04,969
Mediation isn't needed because nothing needs to be mediated.

670
00:22:04,970 --> 00:22:06,879
There's no time to discuss things.

671
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:10,810
Everyone here leaves the moment the shoot ends.

672
00:22:11,210 --> 00:22:13,379
I go around to say bye, but everyone's already gone.

673
00:22:13,380 --> 00:22:15,219
- True.
- No one's around.

674
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:17,749
- I don't remember finding anyone.
- Is that so?

675
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:20,890
You know how cockroaches go into hiding when you open the door?

676
00:22:20,990 --> 00:22:22,830
It's like that. "Good job, everyone."

677
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:25,590
They're gone. It's empty.

678
00:22:25,690 --> 00:22:26,730
"What?"

679
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:28,799
But it must be why the show lasts long.

680
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,269
- Totally.
- It's been over ten years.

681
00:22:30,270 --> 00:22:31,929
Nobody talks gibberish.

682
00:22:31,930 --> 00:22:33,039
- Exactly.
- Yes.

683
00:22:33,040 --> 00:22:34,199
None of us says anything silly.

684
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:36,469
So Sandeul has his own company now.

685
00:22:36,470 --> 00:22:38,469
- Yes.
- You're making a comeback, right?

686
00:22:38,470 --> 00:22:39,609
Aren't you releasing an album?

687
00:22:39,610 --> 00:22:41,509
Yes, we recently made a comeback.

688
00:22:41,510 --> 00:22:42,909
When was it? April when?

689
00:22:42,910 --> 00:22:44,809
- We released an album...
- It's already out.

690
00:22:44,810 --> 00:22:46,450
On April 21.

691
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:48,479
- What's the song title?
- "Rock Paper Scissors."

692
00:22:48,480 --> 00:22:49,789
- "Rock Paper Scissors."
- "Rock Paper Scissors?"

693
00:22:49,790 --> 00:22:50,820
So who won?

694
00:22:51,650 --> 00:22:52,960
I always lose.

695
00:22:53,060 --> 00:22:54,119
Did Gongchan win?

696
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:56,559
We actually split the shapes.

697
00:22:56,560 --> 00:22:59,060
I'm scissors, CNU is rock,

698
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:01,099
and Gongchan is paper.

699
00:23:01,100 --> 00:23:02,359
- Nice.
- Right?

700
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:04,470
Soo Geun, why are they called B1A4?

701
00:23:04,930 --> 00:23:08,000
Explain. There must be viewers who don't know.

702
00:23:08,140 --> 00:23:09,909
- Tell the viewers something.
- Yes.

703
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:11,439
Why is the group called B1A4?

704
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:12,639
- There's a meaning behind it.
- You must know it.

705
00:23:12,640 --> 00:23:13,640
It must have a reason.

706
