- I think I have a scar here.
- That's athlete's foot.

1448
00:51:43,350 --> 00:51:44,819
- Isn't it a stain?
- It's in the middle.

1449
00:51:44,820 --> 00:51:46,350
- That's true.
- That's not it.

1450
00:51:46,620 --> 00:51:48,089
- I think that's the scar.
- So, he does have a scar.

1451
00:51:48,090 --> 00:51:49,559
- It's in the middle.
- It's from last year.

1452
00:51:49,560 --> 00:51:51,829
Gi Kwang, what kind of treatment...

1453
00:51:51,830 --> 00:51:53,829
did you get at the hospital?

1454
00:51:53,830 --> 00:51:55,359
Going to the hospital just because of a digger wasp...

1455
00:51:55,360 --> 00:51:57,330
- shows how weak you are.
- I agree.

1456
00:51:57,900 --> 00:51:59,429
- I mean...
- It's just a digger wasp.

1457
00:51:59,430 --> 00:52:01,369
- Hey.
- After a wasp...

1458
00:52:01,370 --> 00:52:03,039
- My family...
- Right.

1459
00:52:03,040 --> 00:52:04,969
- My father was a beekeeper.
- Soo Geun...

1460
00:52:04,970 --> 00:52:06,839
So, I got stung even after getting under the covers.

1461
00:52:06,840 --> 00:52:09,909
There was a time when he got stung 30 times a day.

1462
00:52:09,910 --> 00:52:12,449
- Seriously?
- It varies from person to person...

1463
00:52:12,450 --> 00:52:14,079
Maybe I should've just applied some doenjang.

1464
00:52:14,080 --> 00:52:15,850
- Let's go.
- Okay. Let's go.

1465
00:52:15,920 --> 00:52:17,249
- Number one.
- It's just...

1466
00:52:17,250 --> 00:52:19,089
"When I don't feel like working out,"

1467
00:52:19,090 --> 00:52:20,589
"I always take my shirt off and look at myself in the mirror."

1468
00:52:20,590 --> 00:52:22,060
Who thinks this is a lie?

1469
00:52:22,290 --> 00:52:24,419
- Why would he take his shirt off?
- I don't get it.

1470
00:52:24,420 --> 00:52:26,059
- Why would he take it off?
- Take off his shirt?

1471
00:52:26,060 --> 00:52:27,406
- Ho Dong.
- He can just weigh himself.

1472
00:52:27,430 --> 00:52:29,129
Number two. "When I have a filming schedule,"

1473
00:52:29,130 --> 00:52:31,829
"I always do fasted cardio in the morning."

1474
00:52:31,830 --> 00:52:34,369
"But when I’m filming with Ho Dong, I always eat a lot of good food."

1475
00:52:34,370 --> 00:52:35,899
- I do the same thing.
- Raise your hands.

1476
00:52:35,900 --> 00:52:37,169
- I think he ate a lot today.
- Hey.

1477
00:52:37,170 --> 00:52:39,569
He says he uses a lot of energy when he's with Ho Dong.

1478
00:52:39,570 --> 00:52:41,439
Number three. "I once went to see flowers by myself."

1479
00:52:41,440 --> 00:52:43,679
"There, I got stung by a bee and bought a lottery ticket."

1480
00:52:43,680 --> 00:52:45,326
Raise your hand if you think this is a lie.

1481
00:52:45,350 --> 00:52:47,609
- Maybe it's his friend's story.
- Why would he buy a lottery ticket?

1482
00:52:47,610 --> 00:52:49,249
- I think the bee part was a lie.
- A friend's story.

1483
00:52:49,250 --> 00:52:50,779
- I agree. It wasn't a bee.
- He didn't get stung by a bee.

1484
00:52:50,780 --> 00:52:52,689
- Did he step on poop?
- It would be something weird.

1485
00:52:52,690 --> 00:52:56,520
Then, which one of Gi Kwang's stories is a lie?

1486
00:52:56,820 --> 00:52:57,920
Tell us.

1487
00:52:58,060 --> 00:52:59,330
My lie is...

1488
00:53:00,030 --> 00:53:02,299
- Which one is the lie?
- Drumroll!

1489
00:53:02,300 --> 00:53:03,960
(What is the one lie that Gi Kwang told?)

1490
00:53:04,560 --> 00:53:05,970
It's number two!

1491
00:53:06,430 --> 00:53:07,430
- Yes!
- Really?

1492
00:53:07,431 --> 00:53:09,199
You said it was...

1493
00:53:09,200 --> 00:53:10,470
- Okay.
- We got it right.

1494
00:53:10,900 --> 00:53:13,239
- I knew it.
- I knew it was a lie.

1495
00:53:13,240 --> 00:53:14,939
He talked too much while telling us number two.

1496
00:53:14,940 --> 00:53:16,309
- Why is it a lie? What's the truth?
- You can get stung by a bee.

1497
00:53:16,310 --> 00:53:18,549
- What?
- Whenever I have...

1498
00:53:18,550 --> 00:53:21,550
a filming schedule, I always do fasted cardio in the morning.

1499
00:53:22,280 --> 00:53:23,720
Then I eat, sticking to a diet menu.

1500
00:53:23,950 --> 00:53:26,349
- Before a shoot?
- Yes. I follow my meal plan.

1501
00:53:26,350 --> 00:53:30,159
It's true that I eat a little more when I have to work with Ho Dong.

1502
00:53:30,160 --> 00:53:31,829
You know, "Cool Kiz on the Block" was a TV show...

1503
00:53:31,830 --> 00:53:33,459
- where I had to exercise a lot.
- It involves physical activity.

1504
00:53:33,460 --> 00:53:34,806
Right. It was a show where we exercised.

1505
00:53:34,830 --> 00:53:35,859
What about "Strong Heart?"

1506
00:53:35,860 --> 00:53:38,499
Maybe because I was doing a TV show at the same time...

1507
00:53:38,500 --> 00:53:40,630
on another channel back then,

1508
00:53:40,770 --> 00:53:42,969
I didn't appear on "Strong Heart" and "Star King."

1509
00:53:42,970 --> 00:53:45,669
You did a TV show with Kim Seung Woo back then.

1510
00:53:45,670 --> 00:53:47,169
- I did "Win Win."
- He did "Win Win" with me.

1511
00:53:47,170 --> 00:53:48,279
I see. On KBS?

1512
00:53:48,280 --> 00:53:50,110
He kept dozing off on "Win Win" back then.

1513
00:53:50,510 --> 00:53:51,579
- He must've been tired.
- He returned from abroad...

1514
00:53:51,580 --> 00:53:52,649
in the morning every time.

1515
00:53:52,650 --> 00:53:55,519
He would come like a machine with no strength and sleep there.

1516
00:53:55,520 --> 00:53:57,149
Did you not scold him?

1517
00:53:57,150 --> 00:53:58,749
- Why would I scold him?
- Shin Young.

1518
00:53:58,750 --> 00:54:00,526
Imagine what it would've been like if it had been "Star King."

1519
00:54:00,550 --> 00:54:02,119
If it had been "Star King..."

1520
00:54:02,120 --> 00:54:03,859
- What if you get caught dozing off?
- He'd be like this.

1521
00:54:03,860 --> 00:54:04,906
(Kim Shin Young's "Star King" Theater)

1522
00:54:04,930 --> 00:54:07,630
He'd go, "What?" But he'd let it slide once.

1523
00:54:08,060 --> 00:54:10,560
Ho Dong would hold it in once.

1524
00:54:11,530 --> 00:54:12,929
- What if you doze off again?
- "Let's take a short break."

1525
00:54:12,930 --> 00:54:13,930
(The "Star King" break)

1526
00:54:14,130 --> 00:54:15,870
"Go ahead."

1527
00:54:16,300 --> 00:54:17,639
"Shin Young, have a seat."

1528
00:54:17,640 --> 00:54:18,670
(Stage 2: Interview)

1529
00:54:18,840 --> 00:54:20,540
"We're professionals!"

1530
00:54:21,810 --> 00:54:22,810
"Are you sleepy?"

1531
00:54:23,480 --> 00:54:26,409
"I can feel the viewers' love,"

1532
00:54:26,410 --> 00:54:27,709
- "Do you feel sleepy?"
- "but you feel sleepy?"

1533
00:54:27,710 --> 00:54:30,420
He'd always go, "Don't you feel bad for the viewers?"

1534
00:54:30,750 --> 00:54:32,919
- "The viewers..."
- "You have no conscience."

1535
00:54:32,920 --> 00:54:34,320
"You have no manners."

1536
00:54:35,090 --> 00:54:37,890
"Did you feel sleepy instead of feeling the love from the viewers?"

1537
00:54:38,790 --> 00:54:40,589
- That's a well-known saying.
- He also said this.

1538
00:54:40,590 --> 00:54:43,059
If you talked too much, Ho Dong would go...

1539
00:54:43,060 --> 00:54:46,029
Let's say there is a live audience sitting in the stands.

1540
00:54:46,030 --> 00:54:47,769
- So he's standing here.
- When you talk too much.

1541
00:54:47,770 --> 00:54:49,699
- What are you doing, Soyou?
- And people are watching. Then...

1542
00:54:49,700 --> 00:54:50,940
- Right. Clap, clap.
- What?

1543
00:54:51,270 --> 00:54:54,169
- Seriously?
- Clap, clap. Shush!

1544
00:54:54,170 --> 00:54:56,040
(Terrifying body language)

1545
00:54:56,510 --> 00:54:58,679
(The third victim shows up thanks to the comrades' efforts.)

1546
00:54:58,680 --> 00:55:00,456
- I look the same, right?
- It's exactly the same.

1547
00:55:00,480 --> 00:55:02,619
- And what else?
- Let's say you're talking...

1548
00:55:02,620 --> 00:55:04,279
- unnecessarily too much.
- Okay.

1549
00:55:04,280 --> 00:55:05,350
It overlaps.

1550
00:55:07,090 --> 00:55:08,490
(Shoo)

1551
00:55:09,820 --> 00:55:12,130
- My goodness.
- What does that mean?

1552
00:55:12,290 --> 00:55:13,389
What is he trying to say?

1553
00:55:13,390 --> 00:55:15,729
Soyou, it looks like you're holding the cue cards now.

1554
00:55:15,730 --> 00:55:16,899
- You look exactly the same.
- So, he's standing like this.

1555
00:55:16,900 --> 00:55:18,630
The star of stars, the king of kings!

1556
00:55:18,970 --> 00:55:21,700
"Don't say anything while I'm talking." I was like this!

1557
00:55:22,270 --> 00:55:24,399
(Shocked)

1558
00:55:24,400 --> 00:55:26,569
- Why are you lying?
- This is absurd!

1559
00:55:26,570 --> 00:55:28,180
(He's saying he feels wronged.)

1560
00:55:28,280 --> 00:55:31,110
- What? You're lying.
- You're a liar.

1561
00:55:31,210 --> 00:55:34,080
- "Stop talking!"
- "We're talking at the same time."

1562
00:55:35,150 --> 00:55:36,519
(The interpretation version is revealed after 12 years.)

1563
00:55:36,520 --> 00:55:38,620
Even Gi Kwang is surprised. It's just absurd.

1564
00:55:39,290 --> 00:55:41,250
- It's unbelievable.
- This is the lie.

1565
00:55:41,420 --> 00:55:43,090
- It's a lie.
- It's the lie we found.

1566
00:55:43,460 --> 00:55:45,730
Our fifth-generation idol, Hanbin.

1567
00:55:45,760 --> 00:55:48,699
What show do the fifth generation want to appear on the most?

1568
00:55:48,700 --> 00:55:50,559
Except for this one. You're appearing on this show now.

1569
00:55:50,560 --> 00:55:51,646
Except for Men on a Mission.

1570
00:55:51,670 --> 00:55:53,106
- Except for Men on a Mission?
- Yes.

1571
00:55:53,130 --> 00:55:54,870
- Is there anything else?
- What was that?

1572
00:55:55,000 --> 00:55:57,139
- Is there anything else?
- What was that?

1573
00:55:57,140 --> 00:55:58,769
- As expected from Hanbin.
- Men on a Mission is the best.

1574
00:55:58,770 --> 00:56:01,640
Hanbin, do you know what Jang Hoon said to me earlier?

1575
00:56:01,840 --> 00:56:05,579
"Hey, Hanbin is really good on air."

1576
00:56:05,580 --> 00:56:07,949
He praised you with a frowning face like this.

1577
00:56:07,950 --> 00:56:09,249
- That's true.
- I mean...

1578
00:56:09,250 --> 00:56:11,019
He's 26, so he has a sense of ease.

1579
00:56:11,020 --> 00:56:15,059
And there aren't many TV shows where idols can appear...

1580
00:56:15,060 --> 00:56:17,089
- and show off their charms.
- This is the one and only show.

1581
00:56:17,090 --> 00:56:18,289
- That's true.
- They can all appear together.

1582
00:56:18,290 --> 00:56:19,759
Right. It's a good thing.

1583
00:56:19,760 --> 00:56:21,599
- Now, let's move on to Soyou.
- All right.

1584
00:56:21,600 --> 00:56:23,330
- Let's go.
- Soyou.

1585
00:56:23,430 --> 00:56:24,629
- Nice.
- Gi Kwang.

1586
00:56:24,630 --> 00:56:25,746
- Gi Kwang.
- You can't do it on "Three Turns."

1587
00:56:25,770 --> 00:56:27,100
(Shoo)

1588
00:56:28,400 --> 00:56:29,669
- All right.
- That's really scary.

1589
00:56:29,670 --> 00:56:31,190
- Gi Kwang.
- If I saw it in person...

1590
00:56:31,610 --> 00:56:35,210
I bet Soyou's lie would also involve Ho Dong.

1591
00:56:35,340 --> 00:56:38,480
No. I'll have to intervene in the editing this week.

1592
00:56:39,080 --> 00:56:41,840
(He announces editorial intervention due to a series of revelations.)

1593
00:56:42,720 --> 00:56:44,119
I'm in a difficult situation.

1594
00:56:44,120 --> 00:56:46,550
You should go to Sangam-dong...

1595
00:56:46,820 --> 00:56:48,360
and stay up all night with them.

1596
00:56:49,320 --> 00:56:50,459
(The body language alert has reached the editing room.)

1597
00:56:50,460 --> 00:56:52,189
- All right.
- That's so funny.

1598
00:56:52,190 --> 00:56:53,589
All right. It's Soyou's turn.

1599
00:56:53,590 --> 00:56:54,959
(Guess Which One is the Lie)

1600
00:56:54,960 --> 00:56:56,030
Soyou, you can begin.

1601
00:56:56,500 --> 00:56:59,470
Number one. My album becomes a hit...

1602
00:56:59,800 --> 00:57:01,800
if I get hurt or cry while preparing for it.

1603
00:57:02,400 --> 00:57:04,039
- It becomes a hit?
- It can happen.

1604
00:57:04,040 --> 00:57:05,369
- It actually happened.
- That's possible.

1605
00:57:05,370 --> 00:57:07,569
- It's like a jinx.
- You get hurt or cry?

1606
00:57:07,570 --> 00:57:09,080
- Okay. Number 2.
- Number 2.

1607
00:57:09,140 --> 00:57:10,879
- Number two.
- I once found...

1608
00:57:10,880 --> 00:57:12,549
a North Korean water bottle on a beach.

1609
00:57:12,550 --> 00:57:14,286
- A North Korean water bottle?
- A North Korean water bottle?

1610
00:57:14,310 --> 00:57:15,679
A water bottle like this floated down?

1611
00:57:15,680 --> 00:57:17,079
- Where?
- An empty bottle.

1612
00:57:17,080 --> 00:57:18,890
- From the Taedong River?
- Number three.

1613
00:57:19,350 --> 00:57:22,359
I love ghost stories so much that I've even visited Salmokji.

1614
00:57:22,360 --> 00:57:24,929
- Why did you do that?
- It's famous now.

1615
00:57:24,930 --> 00:57:26,059
Salmokji.

1616
00:57:26,060 --> 00:57:27,729
- Like the movie?
- Not pork. She said Salmokji.

1617
00:57:27,730 --> 00:57:28,730
The movie, "Salmokji: Whispering Water."

1618
00:57:28,731 --> 00:57:31,130
- You mean the reservoir?
- Come back to the earth.

1619
00:57:31,600 --> 00:57:32,970
Let's start with number one.

1620
00:57:33,170 --> 00:57:35,239
- Tell us about number one.
- Okay.

1621
00:57:35,240 --> 00:57:38,199
It first started when I was working...

1622
00:57:38,200 --> 00:57:40,240
on "Officially Missing You, Too."

1623
00:57:40,540 --> 00:57:43,880
I filmed "Idol Star Wrestling Tournament" the previous day.

1624
00:57:43,980 --> 00:57:46,379
Since I'm an idol, I can't say things like,

1625
00:57:46,380 --> 00:57:47,779
"I can't do this because I'm recording a new song tomorrow."

1626
00:57:47,780 --> 00:57:49,279
- I can't do that, you know.
- Of course not.

1627
00:57:49,280 --> 00:57:51,820
I lost my voice from cheering so hard.

1628
00:57:52,190 --> 00:57:54,690
The intro should start with a soft voice. So, at first...

1629
00:57:55,320 --> 00:57:56,590
"The words..."

1630
00:57:56,690 --> 00:57:58,529
"The words..." I couldn't sing it properly.

1631
00:57:58,530 --> 00:57:59,930
Then the staff came over...

1632
00:58:00,130 --> 00:58:02,430
and said we should cancel the project.

1633
00:58:03,300 --> 00:58:06,829
Since I was the least recognized member of SISTAR,

1634
00:58:06,830 --> 00:58:08,029
it was a golden opportunity...

1635
00:58:08,030 --> 00:58:09,199
- for me.
- Right.

1636
00:58:09,200 --> 00:58:11,870
So I couldn't say a word and just cried.

1637
00:58:11,970 --> 00:58:15,379
Then I said, "I'm really sorry, but I'll go out and get..."

1638
00:58:15,380 --> 00:58:17,139
"some warm water and food."

1639
00:58:17,140 --> 00:58:18,780
That's how I finished the song.

1640
00:58:18,980 --> 00:58:21,079
- And it became a hit.
- It was successful.

1641
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:22,979
And when I was working on this album...

1642
00:58:22,980 --> 00:58:24,549
It was when I was filming...

1643
00:58:24,550 --> 00:58:26,649
- the music video of "Girl."
- "Girl."

1644
00:58:26,650 --> 00:58:27,819
We were going to start the shoot...

1645
00:58:27,820 --> 00:58:28,989
- after a rehearsal.
- Right.

1646
00:58:28,990 --> 00:58:30,959
It was a scene...

1647
00:58:30,960 --> 00:58:33,759
where I turned around on a descending escalator...

1648
00:58:33,760 --> 00:58:35,300
and looked up.

1649
00:58:35,400 --> 00:58:38,429
But as I turned around, I tripped and fell off.

1650
00:58:38,430 --> 00:58:40,269
- What?
- I don't remember the moment.

1651
00:58:40,270 --> 00:58:41,799
- What?
- Were you taken to the hospital?

1652
00:58:41,800 --> 00:58:43,169
- Right away. And...
- She should.

1653
00:58:43,170 --> 00:58:44,469
I got a call from my agency.

1654
00:58:44,470 --> 00:58:46,269
They said they should remove...

1655
00:58:46,270 --> 00:58:48,246
- this scene from the music video.
- It should be removed.

1656
00:58:48,270 --> 00:58:51,410
But I was lying in bed and thought, "No. I have to film this."

1657
00:58:51,980 --> 00:58:54,286
- "I have to do it no matter what."
- You're like singing Kang Ho Dong.

1658
00:58:54,310 --> 00:58:56,619
- "I have to do this."
- "I have to make it."

1659
00:58:56,620 --> 00:58:59,489
I asked the doctor to give me a strong painkiller,

1660
00:58:59,490 --> 00:59:01,860
got an injection, and finished the shoot.

1661
00:59:02,060 --> 00:59:03,366
- It will become a hit, then.
- So...

1662
00:59:03,390 --> 00:59:05,729
Now I'll have to wait and see if it becomes a huge hit.

1663
00:59:05,730 --> 00:59:07,759
I want you to break the jinx.

1664
00:59:07,760 --> 00:59:09,099
- I don't want you to get hurt.
- Right.

1665
00:59:09,100 --> 00:59:10,500
It's not a good thing.

1666
00:59:10,630 --> 00:59:12,229
- I wish it were a lie.
- But I was fine with it.

1667
00:59:12,230 --> 00:59:13,269
- I don't mind it.
- It's a lie,

1668
00:59:13,270 --> 00:59:14,299
but the acting was very good.

1669
00:59:14,300 --> 00:59:15,840
- Right.
- I wish it were a lie.

1670
00:59:16,140 --> 00:59:18,300
- That would be nice.
- This is nonsense.

1671
00:59:18,370 --> 00:59:19,769
It becomes a hit only when she gets hurt?

1672
00:59:19,770 --> 00:59:21,009
- He's right.
- Good.

1673
00:59:21,010 --> 00:59:22,579
- What about number two?
- All right.

1674
00:59:22,580 --> 00:59:25,049
A North Korean water bottle. How did it happen?

1675
00:59:25,050 --> 00:59:27,549
There was a time when I was really into surfing.

1676
00:59:27,550 --> 00:59:29,019
- Right. She was into surfing.
- I see.

1677
00:59:29,020 --> 00:59:32,319
The waves are good in the mornings.

1678
00:59:32,320 --> 00:59:33,720
